## 1. üéØ Core Typography Principles

### 1.1. Legibility vs Readability
- **Legibility**: How easy individual characters are to distinguish
- **Readability**: How easy text is to read in longer passages
- Both are essential but serve different purposes

### 1.2. Type Hierarchy
- Establish clear levels: H1 > H2 > H3 > Body > Caption
- Use size, weight, and color to create distinction
- Maintain consistent ratios between levels

### 1.3. Optimal Line Length
- **50-75 characters per line** for optimal readability
- Use `max-width: 65ch` for body content
- Shorter for mobile, longer for wide screens

### 1.4. Line Height (Leading)
- **Body text**: 1.5-1.75 for comfortable reading
- **Headings**: 1.1-1.3 for tighter spacing
- **Captions**: 1.4-1.6 for clarity

### 1.5. Font Performance
- Limit font weights and styles loaded
- Use variable fonts when appropriate
- Subset fonts to include only needed characters
- Use system fonts for instant loading

## 2. ‚úÖ DO (Recommended Practices)

### 2.1. Font Selection

#### Choosing Web Fonts
- ‚úÖ **Consider readability first**: Not all fonts work on screens
- ‚úÖ **Limit to 2-3 font families maximum**
- ‚úÖ **Test at small sizes**: Ensure legibility at 14-16px
- ‚úÖ **Check character support**: Verify complete character sets

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Limited font families with clear purposes */
:root {
  /* Headings: Geometric sans-serif for impact */
  --font-heading: 'Inter', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
  
  /* Body: Highly readable sans-serif */
  --font-body: 'Inter', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
  
  /* Monospace: Code and technical content */
  --font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', 'Consolas', monospace;
}

/* Using system font stack for maximum performance */
:root {
  --font-system: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 
                 'Segoe UI', 'Roboto', 'Oxygen', 'Ubuntu', 
                 'Cantarell', 'Fira Sans', 'Droid Sans', 
                 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;
}

body {
  font-family: var(--font-body);
}

h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
  font-family: var(--font-heading);
}

code, pre {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
}
```

#### Font Pairing
- ‚úÖ **Contrast is key**: Pair serif + sans-serif or geometric + humanist
- ‚úÖ **Same family different weights**: Simplest and safest
- ‚úÖ **Test together**: Ensure fonts complement each other
- ‚úÖ **Consider mood alignment**: Fonts should match brand tone

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Single family (safest) */
:root {
  --font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
}

/* ‚úÖ Good: Font pairing */
:root {
  --font-heading: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
  --font-body: 'Merriweather', serif;
}
```

### 2.2. Type Scale System

#### Modular Scale
- ‚úÖ **Use consistent ratio**: 1.2 (Minor Third), 1.25 (Major Third), 1.333 (Perfect Fourth), 1.5 (Perfect Fifth)
- ‚úÖ **Define complete scale**: From smallest to largest
- ‚úÖ **Use CSS variables**: For easy maintenance
- ‚úÖ **Test on actual devices**: Ensure sizes work in context

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Modular scale with 1.25 ratio */
:root {
  --text-base: 1rem;
  --text-sm: 0.8rem;
  --text-lg: 1.25rem;
  --text-xl: 1.563rem;
  --text-2xl: 1.953rem;
}

h1 { font-size: var(--text-2xl); }
h2 { font-size: var(--text-xl); }
p { font-size: var(--text-base); }
```

#### Fluid Typography with clamp()
- ‚úÖ **Scale smoothly between breakpoints**
- ‚úÖ **Use clamp() for automatic scaling**
- ‚úÖ **Define min, preferred, and max sizes**
- ‚úÖ **Test at various screen widths**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Fluid typography */
:root {
  --text-base: clamp(1rem, 0.95rem + 0.25vw, 1.125rem);
  --text-xl: clamp(1.25rem, 1.1rem + 0.75vw, 2rem);
  --text-2xl: clamp(1.5rem, 1.3rem + 1vw, 2.5rem);
}

h1 { font-size: var(--text-2xl); }
body { font-size: var(--text-base); }
```

### 2.3. Line Height and Spacing

#### Line Height Guidelines
- ‚úÖ **Body text: 1.5-1.75** for comfortable reading
- ‚úÖ **Headings: 1.1-1.3** for tighter, impactful spacing
- ‚úÖ **Small text: 1.4-1.6** for clarity
- ‚úÖ **Adjust with font size**: Larger text = tighter leading

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Line height system */
:root {
  --leading-tight: 1.25;
  --leading-normal: 1.5;
  --leading-relaxed: 1.625;
}

h1, h2 { line-height: var(--leading-tight); }
p { line-height: var(--leading-normal); }
article p { line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); }
```

#### Letter Spacing (Tracking)
- ‚úÖ **Uppercase: increase spacing (+0.05-0.1em)**
- ‚úÖ **Small text: slight increase (+0.01-0.02em)**
- ‚úÖ **Large headings: slight decrease (-0.01-0.02em)**
- ‚úÖ **Body text: usually default (0)**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Letter spacing */
h1, h2 {
  letter-spacing: -0.025em;
}

.uppercase {
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}

p {
  letter-spacing: 0;
}
```

### 2.4. Line Length and Measure

#### Optimal Line Length
- ‚úÖ **50-75 characters per line** (65ch optimal)
- ‚úÖ **Use `ch` unit** for character-based width
- ‚úÖ **Narrower for mobile** (45-60 characters)
- ‚úÖ **Consider reading context**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Optimal line length */
.prose {
  max-width: 65ch;
  margin: 0 auto;
}
```

### 2.5. Font Loading and Performance

#### Modern Font Loading
- ‚úÖ **Use `font-display: swap`** for faster perceived load
- ‚úÖ **Preload critical fonts**
- ‚úÖ **Subset fonts** to reduce file size
- ‚úÖ **Consider variable fonts** for flexibility with one file

```html
<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Preload critical fonts -->
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>

<!-- Preload the most critical font -->
<link rel="preload" 
      href="/fonts/inter-var.woff2" 
      as="font" 
      type="font/woff2" 
      crossorigin>

<!-- Load fonts with font-display: swap -->
<style>
  @font-face {
    font-family: 'Inter';
    src: url('/fonts/inter-var.woff2') format('woff2');
    font-weight: 100 900;           /* Variable font weight range */
    font-display: swap;             /* Show fallback immediately */
    font-style: normal;
  }
</style>
```

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Font loading with fallback system */
:root {
  --font-primary: 'Inter', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
}

body {
  font-family: var(--font-primary);
  font-weight: 400;
  /* Browser shows system font immediately, swaps when Inter loads */
}

/* ‚úÖ Good: Limit font weights loaded */
/* Only load weights you actually use */
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600;700&display=swap');

/* ‚ùå Bad: Loading all weights */
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@100;200;300;400;500;600;700;800;900&display=swap');
```

#### Variable Fonts
- ‚úÖ **One file, multiple weights/styles**
- ‚úÖ **Better performance than multiple files**
- ‚úÖ **Smooth interpolation between weights**
- ‚úÖ **Growing browser support**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Variable font usage */
@font-face {
  font-family: 'Inter';
  src: url('/fonts/Inter-VariableFont.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-weight: 100 900;           /* Supports any weight in this range */
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}

h1 {
  font-family: 'Inter';
  font-weight: 750;               /* Can use any value between 100-900 */
}

h2 {
  font-weight: 650;
}

p {
  font-weight: 400;
}

strong {
  font-weight: 600;
}
```

### 2.6. Text Formatting

#### Emphasis and Hierarchy
- ‚úÖ **Use semantic HTML**: `<strong>`, `<em>`, `<mark>`
- ‚úÖ **Limit emphasis**: Don't bold everything
- ‚úÖ **Consistent formatting**: Apply styles consistently
- ‚úÖ **Readable paragraphs**: Use spacing between paragraphs

```html
<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Semantic emphasis -->
<article>
  <h1>Article Title</h1>
  <p>Paragraph with <strong>important information</strong>.</p>
  <p>We can emphasize <em>specific words</em> when needed.</p>
</article>
```

## 3. ‚ùå DON'T (Anti-patterns)

### 3.1. Font Selection Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Too many fonts**: Don't use more than 2-3 families
- ‚ùå **Decorative body text**: Don't use display fonts for paragraphs
- ‚ùå **Poor readability**: Don't sacrifice legibility for style
- ‚ùå **Inconsistent fonts**: Don't mix fonts randomly

```css
/* ‚ùå Bad: Too many fonts */
h1 { font-family: 'Font1'; }
h2 { font-family: 'Font2'; }
p { font-family: 'Font3'; }

/* ‚úÖ Good: Consistent system */
:root {
  --font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
}
h1, h2, p { font-family: var(--font-family); }
```

### 3.2. Size and Scale Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Random sizes**: Don't use arbitrary font sizes
- ‚ùå **Too small**: Don't use less than 14px for body text
- ‚ùå **Insufficient contrast**: Don't make headings too similar
- ‚ùå **Inconsistent scaling**: Don't break the type scale

```css
/* ‚ùå Bad: Random sizes */
h1 { font-size: 37px; }
h2 { font-size: 29px; }
p { font-size: 15px; }

/* ‚úÖ Good: Systematic scale */
h1 { font-size: var(--text-2xl); }
h2 { font-size: var(--text-xl); }
p { font-size: var(--text-base); }
```

### 3.3. Line Height Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Too tight**: Don't use line-height below 1.4 for body
- ‚ùå **Too loose**: Don't use excessive leading
- ‚ùå **Same for all**: Don't use one line-height everywhere
- ‚ùå **Fixed pixels**: Don't use px for line-height

```css
/* ‚ùå Bad: Too tight */
p { line-height: 1.2; }

/* ‚ùå Bad: Using pixels */
p { font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; }

/* ‚úÖ Good: Appropriate line-heights */
h1, h2 { line-height: 1.25; }
p { line-height: 1.6; }
```

### 3.4. Line Length Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Too long**: Don't let lines exceed 90 characters
- ‚ùå **Too short**: Don't constrain to less than 40 characters
- ‚ùå **No limits**: Don't let text span full width on wide screens
- ‚ùå **Ignoring content**: Don't use same width for all content

```css
/* ‚ùå Bad: No limit */
.article { width: 100%; }

/* ‚úÖ Good: Optimal line length */
.article { max-width: 65ch; margin: 0 auto; }
```

### 3.5. Performance Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Loading all weights**: Don't load unused font weights
- ‚ùå **No font-display**: Don't cause FOIT (flash of invisible text)
- ‚ùå **Not subsetting**: Don't load entire font with unused glyphs
- ‚ùå **Multiple font services**: Don't load from multiple CDNs

```html
<!-- ‚ùå Bad: Loading all weights unnecessarily -->
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@100;200;300;400;500;600;700;800;900&display=swap">

<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Only load needed weights -->
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600;700&display=swap">
```

